# Telnet Queue

The purpose of Telnet Queue is to send commands in a specified amount of time to a certain connection.

## Requirements

* 64-bit Windows Computer
* Have PuTTY installed with valid collector connections

## Accepted Filetypes

Accepts CSV format, character delimiter must be either a comma, or newline. By selecting a file each entry will execute
the command entered(replacing ***$1*** with each entry)

## Clients

This lists all available PuTTY sessions, which should contain mostly utility/client connections.

## Gateways

Once a Client is selected, this will show ALL gateways(Including Offline). The gateway list also includes -1 selection
which lets a command be executed on each gateway for a client.

## Commands

Each line entered will be executed on every MIU listed in the CSV, use ***$1*** for MIU number placeholder.

For example,

_Commands:_

```
rexec $1 "meter roll 6"
rexec $1 "meter trunc 0"
```

_File Contents:_

```
123456,654321
```

*or*

```
123456
654321
```

This execution would run ```rexec 123456 "meter roll 6"```, then after the specified Queue Wait set it'll
execute ```rexec 123456 "meter trunc 0"```.

Then after the specified Queue Wait passes again, then it'll do the same thing but replacing ```123456```
with ```654321```

## Queue Wait

If set above zero then it'll wait in between command executions. Wait must be in minutes

## Progress Bar

This shows the progress of the current execution. Once "Execute" is pressed there'll also be a Remaining Time label and
a percentage representative of the execution progress.

## Execute

Well... It executes the listed commands on each MIU listed.
